India Equities Mover: Shopper’s Stop, UTV Software, Wockhardt

-- B y   S h i k h a r   B a l w a n i   a n d   H e m a l   S a v a i
-- 
2011-07-26T12:15:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/india-stock-movers-sterlite-industries-utv-software.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3:30 p.m. close in Mumbai.  India ’s Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
declined 353.07 points, or 1.9 percent, to 18,518.22. The BSE200
Index fell 1.6 percent to 2,301.06.  Shopper’s Stop Ltd. (SHOP)   sank 4.7 percent to 445.6
rupees, its lowest in a month. The second-largest publicly
traded retailer reported loss of 15.2 million rupees from 92.9
million profit year earlier.  UTV Software Communications Ltd. (UTV)   climbed 5.4
percent to 950.15 rupees, its highest since Dec. 14, 2007. The
movie and television content maker said it plans to delist its
shares from all  stock exchanges . Walt Disney Co. will acquire
19.8 percent of UTV from its founders, the company said in an
exchange filing. The company will buy back public shares at up
to 1,000 rupees a share.  Wockhardt Ltd. (WPL)  , the drugmaker, gained 4 percent to
434.5 rupees, its highest since Jan. 2, 2008, after the Economic
Times reported that Danone is in discussions to buy its
nutrition business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
